1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:03,050 --> 00:00:04,650
That shampoo also costs a fortune.

3
00:00:05,750 --> 00:00:07,350
Hi, oh, I'll take some.

4
00:00:07,890 --> 00:00:08,850
That's the score.

5
00:00:09,210 --> 00:00:09,490
What?

6
00:00:09,850 --> 00:00:10,710
What score?

7
00:00:11,050 --> 00:00:14,150
My ex wants one kid in his custody, so I'm deciding which one to give him.

8
00:00:14,350 --> 00:00:15,790
Sasa's in the lead so far.

9
00:00:15,790 --> 00:00:16,230
What?

10
00:00:17,190 --> 00:00:20,330
How can he suddenly want a kid when he never took care of them?

11
00:00:20,530 --> 00:00:22,730
Well, he built a house and needs someone to mow the lawn.

12
00:00:24,260 --> 00:00:24,880
Hi, mom.

13
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:25,880
Hi, Lexa.

14
00:00:25,920 --> 00:00:26,180
Dude.

15
00:00:26,750 --> 00:00:27,650
How was school?

16
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,260
Normal, failed physics.

17
00:00:29,420 --> 00:00:29,600
Okay.

18
00:00:30,260 --> 00:00:33,120
Oh, and the homeroom teacher says you need to come in about the torched locker rooms.

19
00:00:33,420 --> 00:00:33,580
Sure.

20
00:00:35,340 --> 00:00:36,860
Oh, and I lost the apartment keys.

21
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:37,900
Of course.

22
00:00:38,650 --> 00:00:39,800
Your lunch is in the kitchen.

23
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:40,080
Yeah.

24
00:00:44,050 --> 00:00:44,900
Hi, Sasa.

25
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:49,860
Today a career counselor came to school and said I could go to college for education.

26
00:00:49,860 --> 00:00:52,900
And how long would I have to support you?

27
00:00:53,180 --> 00:00:54,220
It's only five years.

28
00:00:55,950 --> 00:01:00,250
Yeah, it's a drama.

29
00:01:01,870 --> 00:01:03,350
But please, don't tell anyone.

30
00:01:03,490 --> 00:01:04,890
They'd just make a mess of it, right?

31
00:01:06,350 --> 00:01:07,850
I took two extra dumplings.

32
00:01:11,650 --> 00:01:12,140
You can go.

33
00:01:12,350 --> 00:01:13,250
No, I'm not hungry.

34
00:01:15,850 --> 00:01:17,170
Today I dreamed about dad.

35
00:01:17,450 --> 00:01:19,950
In the dream we were all together again.

36
00:01:20,250 --> 00:01:21,250
Sure.

37
00:01:23,550 --> 00:01:26,950
Wait, you can't just let Libor blackmail you like this.

38
00:01:27,550 --> 00:01:32,350
At the divorce, the judge told me she's only giving me the kids because Libor doesn't want them and the orphanages are full.

39
00:01:32,650 --> 00:01:34,250
Can you zip up my vest?

40
00:01:37,450 --> 00:01:38,050
Thanks, mom.

41
00:01:38,550 --> 00:01:40,550
Everyone's the architect of their own happiness.

42
00:01:42,030 --> 00:02:19,510
What's going on?

43
00:02:20,150 --> 00:02:25,250
I wanted to tell you that I love you very much regardless of how much you eat or what you do in life.

44
00:02:25,460 --> 00:02:26,240
Great.

45
00:02:32,250 --> 00:02:33,950
And what happened at school?

46
00:02:34,950 --> 00:02:35,650
What do you think?

47
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:36,330
Nothing.

48
00:02:37,050 --> 00:02:39,610
Sasa said you went to the career counselor.

49
00:02:39,850 --> 00:02:40,650
Yeah, we did.

50
00:02:41,850 --> 00:02:42,680
What did he say to Lexa?

51
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,680
Why do you care?

52
00:02:43,780 --> 00:02:44,100
Just curious.

53
00:02:44,950 --> 00:02:47,550
Same as always, that he's a career counselor, not a psychiatrist.

54
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:49,750
Poor Lexa.

55
00:02:50,220 --> 00:02:50,640
Why?

56
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:51,060
No reason.

57
00:02:52,050 --> 00:02:54,650
And aren't you even curious what he said to me, since we love each other so much?

58
00:02:54,650 --> 00:02:55,990
So what did he say to you, Ivuska?

59
00:02:56,550 --> 00:02:57,150
Nothing.

60
00:02:58,050 --> 00:03:02,350
That the conservatory is a dumb idea, that I should improve my math and try business school.

61
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:05,450
Based on what he tells Lexa, he seems like a sensible guy.

62
00:03:05,850 --> 00:03:07,640
And what's wrong with wanting to be an actress?

63
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:09,440
I'm the best in the school drama club.

64
00:03:09,620 --> 00:03:11,500
Last time I saw you, you were playing a dog.

65
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:13,060
That was in elementary school.

66
00:03:13,180 --> 00:03:15,060
It was Tyrl and we were doing Grandmother.

67
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,820
Who was supposed to tell it was Grandmother when you were all eight?

68
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:18,920
You should come now.

69
00:03:19,350 --> 00:03:21,950
We're rehearsing the Passion plays and I'm playing Mary Magdalene.

70
00:03:22,650 --> 00:03:23,250
And Sasa?

71
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:24,400
Judas.

72
00:03:24,650 --> 00:03:25,750
Nobody wanted that part.

73
00:03:26,050 --> 00:03:27,450
But it'll be great.

74
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:30,250
Hi, Iva.

75
00:03:30,350 --> 00:03:31,710
I signed up for the drama club.

76
00:03:31,790 --> 00:03:32,510
It won't be great.

77
00:03:32,830 --> 00:03:34,430
I got some guy called Jesus.

78
00:03:34,730 --> 00:03:36,630
I hope we'll have some kissing scene.

79
00:03:36,930 --> 00:03:41,510
The hour is nigh in which the will of my father the creator shall be fulfilled.

80
00:03:41,670 --> 00:03:45,310
My tearful mother, grieve not, for we must bid each other farewell.

81
00:03:46,490 --> 00:03:47,050
Awesome.

82
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:49,250
What does that mean?

83
00:03:49,250 --> 00:03:52,350
That you should give me those dumplings.

84
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:04,520
Here are the apartment keys.

85
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:07,020
This is the key to the back door of the pub, okay.

86
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:07,840
Give that one to Ozzak.

87
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:11,160
And please ask Iva to cover for Sasa next week at the meeting, okay.

88
00:04:11,180 --> 00:04:11,520
Thanks.

89
00:04:12,250 --> 00:04:13,460
God, what's going on?

90
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:19,520
Oh please, I had a weak moment, ate all the pretzels and called Libor that I'm keeping both kids.

91
00:04:19,520 --> 00:04:20,500
Good for you.

92
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,240
He called social services on me.

93
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:22,900
So we're leaving.

94
00:04:23,140 --> 00:04:23,760
For God's sake, where?

95
00:04:24,450 --> 00:04:26,520
We have enough money to get to Valasske Mezirici.

96
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,260
Then we'll see.

97
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:28,520
I'm off then.

98
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:32,030
Wait, mothers always have it good with social services.

99
00:04:32,050 --> 00:04:37,450
Not the mothers who work nights, sleep days, and believe their kids can take care of themselves.

100
00:04:38,550 --> 00:04:40,750
You can't raise kids on the run.

101
00:04:41,050 --> 00:04:42,350
Haven't you seen Terminator?

102
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:47,250
Wait, couldn't you just call social services and tell them everything's fine at home?

103
00:04:48,450 --> 00:04:49,950
Lie to social services?

104
00:04:50,970 --> 00:04:52,130
Why didn't I think of that.

105
00:04:52,910 --> 00:04:54,830
I really am going through a rough patch.

106
00:05:03,450 --> 00:05:04,810
Hey Mr. Ozzak, happy birthday.

107
00:05:04,810 --> 00:05:05,110
Hi.

108
00:05:05,450 --> 00:05:06,470
Aren't you in school?

109
00:05:06,650 --> 00:05:08,850
We were supposed to visit our aunt in Valmez, but it fell through.

110
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:09,430
Weird.

111
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:12,650
I didn't even know we had an aunt in Valmez.

112
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:13,890
I need some advice.

113
00:05:14,050 --> 00:05:16,450
I'm in the drama club and I'm playing some Jesus guy.

114
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:19,470
Well, Mr. Ozzak is probably not an expert on that.

115
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:23,030
Actually, I was once interested in these things.

116
00:05:23,830 --> 00:05:25,530
Don't tell me you actually set foot in a church.

117
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:26,630
Of course I did.

118
00:05:27,450 --> 00:05:28,950
And immediately walked back out.

119
00:05:29,030 --> 00:05:30,770
I got a really nasty feeling there.

120
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:33,410
When I grabbed some wine to wash it down, they yelled at me that I'm a Hussite.

121
00:05:33,810 --> 00:05:37,330
Besides, I think if they served beer there, it would attract way more people.

122
00:05:38,750 --> 00:05:40,270
What exactly do you need advice on?

123
00:05:41,050 --> 00:05:43,250
Well, Jesus and Mary Magdalene.

124
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,970
Whether they ever kissed.

125
00:05:46,210 --> 00:05:47,190
I'm afraid not.

126
00:05:47,450 --> 00:05:49,530
Their relationship was purely spiritual.

127
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:51,650
Spiritual.

128
00:05:53,450 --> 00:05:54,950
So no making out?

129
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:57,750
I think she once washed his feet.

130
00:05:58,550 --> 00:05:59,070
Great.

131
00:05:59,070 --> 00:06:02,930
So on top of everything, I'll have to bring clean socks every time.

132
00:06:02,930 --> 00:06:03,530
Don't you want him?

133
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:05,040
Yeah.

134
00:06:06,050 --> 00:06:07,850
Jesus Christ Superstar.

135
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:10,750
I don't think he's released anything else yet.

136
00:06:24,450 --> 00:06:25,090
She's coming.

137
00:06:28,010 --> 00:06:29,450
Can we put stuff on your couch?

138
00:06:29,690 --> 00:06:31,270
What are you doing?

139
00:06:32,010 --> 00:06:33,850
Mom said we should bring our stuff to your place.

140
00:06:33,930 --> 00:06:35,870
And if anyone asks, we shouldn't say anything.

141
00:06:36,010 --> 00:06:37,010
Probably some kind of adventure game.

142
00:06:37,850 --> 00:06:40,110
Like when she first saw Terminator.

143
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:42,050
We slept in a junkyard for a week.

144
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:44,850
Well, Simona.

145
00:06:46,650 --> 00:06:47,950
So Sasa wouldn't get bored.

146
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,400
What's this supposed to mean?

147
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:54,080
I went to social services to tell them they don't live unsupervised in some squalid dump and that they're well taken care of.

148
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:54,560
And what did they say?

149
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,240
That they'll come and check.

150
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:59,150
So you want to make them believe you live in my apartment?

151
00:06:59,350 --> 00:07:02,820
They said it's good I have a partner, at least Lexa won't be missing a male role model.

152
00:07:02,820 --> 00:07:04,520
I'm not going to lie to social services.

153
00:07:05,450 --> 00:07:07,050
Sasa, Lexa!

154
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:10,040
Auntie from Valmez called, she's feeling better, so we're going!

155
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:14,040
Wait, cut it out, isn't there any other option?

156
00:07:14,850 --> 00:07:19,550
There's the creep from the third floor, he offered himself, if I let him sleep on the cot with Lexa.

157
00:07:20,150 --> 00:07:24,450
Mom, but today we have to go, we have the rehearsal for the play.

158
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:29,420
Suffer the little children to come unto me and forbid them not, for of such...

159
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:31,450
Is the kingdom of God.

160
00:07:32,950 --> 00:07:34,650
I studied that for seven hours.

161
00:07:35,450 --> 00:07:37,550
Lexa, but that part was cut.

162
00:07:41,550 --> 00:07:42,650
Fine then.

163
00:07:43,650 --> 00:07:45,150
So we don't have to go today.

164
00:07:45,350 --> 00:07:48,050
Hopefully her health will hold out for a few days.

165
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:49,360
Or weeks.

166
00:07:50,930 --> 00:07:52,250
They said up to three months.

167
00:07:54,650 --> 00:07:56,700
Great, today we're rehearsing the Last Supper.

168
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:58,020
Great, so we'll eat there.

169
00:07:58,260 --> 00:07:58,840
Great.

170
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:07,590
For the last time, Sasa plays Judas.

171
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:09,250
But you'd be a much better Judas.

172
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:14,750
He found out Judas kisses Jesus and wants to switch casting.

173
00:08:14,770 --> 00:08:16,270
It can't be taken off at home.

174
00:08:19,650 --> 00:08:20,550
Is something wrong?

175
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:24,890
You always look like this when you're about to give a speech about hard times ahead.

176
00:08:24,890 --> 00:08:26,550
Oh, can I listen too?

177
00:08:26,550 --> 00:08:30,850
Mom hates this stuff so she always writes it on the fridge and hides in the pantry.

178
00:08:32,050 --> 00:08:34,050
I'd like to talk to Iva alone first.

179
00:08:36,510 --> 00:08:38,150
Dad called social services on us.

180
00:08:38,190 --> 00:08:41,210
We have to pretend we're one family with the Pacovskys, or you'll end up in a children's home.

181
00:08:41,490 --> 00:08:42,890
Switch the nameplates on the doors.

182
00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:45,750
Go after him.

183
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:46,680
Dad?

184
00:08:51,550 --> 00:08:52,750
Any questions?

185
00:08:53,250 --> 00:08:55,050
Do you know how I can get this off?

186
00:08:55,460 --> 00:08:55,960
Ouch.

187
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:57,080
Thanks, mom.

188
00:09:08,350 --> 00:09:15,150
Sasa will sleep with Iva in her room, Lexa will set up the cot, and Simona won't come until morning, so we don't need to worry about her.

189
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,400
I'm not sleeping with Sasa.

190
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:19,480
You meant to say with Lexa?

191
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:20,720
I meant to say with Sasa.

192
00:09:21,450 --> 00:09:21,980
Iva...

193
00:09:22,250 --> 00:09:24,550
Everyone knows you review your school material in your sleep.

194
00:09:24,650 --> 00:09:26,110
I'll never forget that school trip.

195
00:09:26,730 --> 00:09:28,190
Names of Czech rulers.

196
00:09:28,650 --> 00:09:30,110
Those were dates for history class.

197
00:09:30,110 --> 00:09:31,710
And I ended up getting an A.

198
00:09:32,230 --> 00:09:34,150
Then you'll sleep with me, like when you were little.

199
00:09:34,750 --> 00:09:38,050
Great, and I'll go back to the therapist because of those dreams about a dying elephant.

200
00:09:38,550 --> 00:09:40,390
I snore a little, big deal.

201
00:09:40,650 --> 00:09:43,050
Then sleep with Ozzak, nothing ever wakes him up.

202
00:09:43,050 --> 00:09:46,950
Ozzak will have to sleep on the couch because his room is our weak spot.

203
00:09:47,070 --> 00:09:47,510
Why?

204
00:09:48,150 --> 00:09:51,270
The social workers might think we have an illegal dump in there.

205
00:09:51,350 --> 00:09:53,390
We need to somehow barricade that room.

206
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:53,770
Hi.

207
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,120
Isn't our weak spot actually Ozzak?

208
00:09:56,120 --> 00:10:01,950
That's fine because Simona told social services we're taking care of a mentally handicapped cousin named Igor.

209
00:10:03,050 --> 00:10:06,390
I'm curious who's going to explain to Ozzak that he can't go in his own room.

210
00:10:06,390 --> 00:10:06,910
Simona.

211
00:10:08,950 --> 00:10:09,950
Sure.

212
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:20,530
Ozzy Osbourne really called and said he can't go in his own room?

213
00:10:21,050 --> 00:10:22,050
That seems weird to me.

214
00:10:23,350 --> 00:10:25,650
Normally bro just calls to tell me to clean the basement.

215
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:30,710
But it's nice having a buddy, huh?

216
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:36,450
One more then.

217
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:40,650
If only everything in life were this simple.

218
00:10:52,550 --> 00:10:54,550
Cool guy, that Jesus.

219
00:10:54,950 --> 00:10:57,950
They nailed him to a cross, he survived and came back like the Terminator.

220
00:11:01,850 --> 00:11:03,150
I probably don't have the whole thing.

221
00:11:03,850 --> 00:11:08,050
Now there has to be the part where he goes to kick Judas's ass.

222
00:11:08,550 --> 00:11:09,850
Because I'm pretty sure it was him who betrayed him.

223
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:18,260
Judas hangs himself and dangles till the end of the show.

224
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:19,960
And there's a terrible draft on his feet.

225
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:23,650
Damn, read the key passages.

226
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:26,550
Okay, so Judas is taken care of, but what about the others?

227
00:11:26,850 --> 00:11:27,550
Pilate.

228
00:11:27,950 --> 00:11:29,150
Lexa, it doesn't go further.

229
00:11:29,850 --> 00:11:33,580
I don't get it, if it was really that successful, why didn't someone make a sequel?

230
00:11:37,950 --> 00:11:40,250
So how's it going, kids?

231
00:11:40,410 --> 00:11:40,970
Not great.

232
00:11:41,550 --> 00:11:44,450
Lexa is rambling and Sasa is whimpering.

233
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:50,200
Blessed are the wombs that never bore, the breasts that never nursed.

234
00:11:50,650 --> 00:11:53,240
But I really don't get why I have to talk like an idiot.

235
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:53,920
Nobody here does.

236
00:11:55,220 --> 00:11:56,520
Come on Iva, don't be nasty.

237
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:59,180
Is it really that hard to be nice to your friend?

238
00:11:59,180 --> 00:12:03,480
Lexa isn't my friend and he's never lying around in my living room founding new religions.

239
00:12:03,820 --> 00:12:07,360
Oh come on, what kind of people would we be if we couldn't help each other out?

240
00:12:09,150 --> 00:12:09,750
I'm going to bed.

241
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:11,950
Me too.

242
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:14,060
Not anywhere else.

243
00:12:14,060 --> 00:12:17,350
Don't worry, now that we're grown-ups, I'm not scared.

244
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:17,920
Good night.

245
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:18,640
Good night.

246
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:18,980
Night.

247
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:37,270
Twenty.

248
00:12:38,650 --> 00:12:39,150
Twenty-one.

249
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:40,480
Twenty-two.

250
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:41,280
Lexa.

251
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:44,050
Lexa, wake up and go to my room.

252
00:12:45,950 --> 00:12:47,190
Iva, finally!

253
00:12:47,190 --> 00:12:50,650
Judas is counting silver coins and I can't fall asleep.

254
00:12:50,940 --> 00:12:52,000
So no sex?

255
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,040
No, get out!

256
00:12:54,850 --> 00:12:58,450
Three, four, five.

257
00:13:13,150 --> 00:13:14,450
Jesus, I don't have a bed.

258
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:17,350
I can reach the ceiling.

259
00:13:17,790 --> 00:13:18,770
Uncle, be quiet.

260
00:13:18,770 --> 00:13:21,850
Ivuska, I excelled myself.

261
00:13:21,950 --> 00:13:27,050
This place is a disaster.

262
00:13:27,550 --> 00:13:30,650
Sorry, I forgot what I promised big Ozzak.

263
00:13:31,450 --> 00:13:32,350
Are you sleeping on the couch?

264
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,050
No, you're sleeping at dad's.

265
00:13:35,950 --> 00:13:37,160
But I'll clean the basement tomorrow.

266
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:41,650
And who sleeps on the couch?

267
00:13:41,650 --> 00:13:43,790
And why?

268
00:13:44,650 --> 00:13:45,620
Because of Judas.

269
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:49,550
And why can't Ozzak sleep on the cot?

270
00:13:51,150 --> 00:13:51,680
You'll see.

271
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:06,550
I forgot that Ozzak can't fall asleep any other way.

272
00:14:23,950 --> 00:14:24,490
I don't want to be here.

273
00:14:24,850 --> 00:14:25,750
There's an elephant here.

274
00:14:26,850 --> 00:14:27,390
Dad, there.

275
00:14:27,650 --> 00:14:28,550
That's Ozzak.

276
00:14:29,850 --> 00:14:31,950
You must be able to figure this out by now.

277
00:14:52,770 --> 00:14:53,710
Hold on, hold on.

278
00:14:54,050 --> 00:14:55,330
Leave it, dad.

279
00:14:55,430 --> 00:14:57,010
He doesn't want me anymore anyway.

280
00:14:57,830 --> 00:15:18,670
I can't fall asleep.

281
00:15:20,350 --> 00:15:21,650
There's way too much light from these white walls.

282
00:15:22,050 --> 00:15:23,060
Turn the TV back off.

283
00:15:23,060 --> 00:15:23,820
And put it where?

284
00:15:24,450 --> 00:15:25,450
Figure it out.

285
00:15:39,850 --> 00:15:40,350
Kids, I'm home.

286
00:15:44,650 --> 00:15:46,310
Tomas, how are you managing here?

287
00:15:46,310 --> 00:15:46,450
What?

288
00:15:46,530 --> 00:15:46,930
What?

289
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:49,550
How did you get in here?

290
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:51,550
I don't know.

291
00:15:51,850 --> 00:15:53,610
It's nice in here.

292
00:15:53,610 --> 00:15:54,850
I'll just lie down.

293
00:15:54,970 --> 00:15:55,410
Good night.

294
00:15:55,790 --> 00:15:56,210
Good night.

295
00:15:58,550 --> 00:16:00,140
What's that walking around?

296
00:16:11,350 --> 00:16:12,650
How are you without the orphanage?

297
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:14,960
I had a terrible dream.

298
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:18,340
Some people were chasing me from one room to another.

299
00:16:18,350 --> 00:16:20,650
I was rescuing elephants.

300
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:23,250
This isn't going to work.

301
00:16:23,450 --> 00:16:27,550
We need to get organized so Ozzak doesn't have to sleep in the bathroom.

302
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:32,690
I'm calling Simona to say I want my room back.

303
00:16:32,690 --> 00:16:34,250
She's sleeping now, don't bother her.

304
00:16:37,950 --> 00:16:39,400
I'll make a new sleeping plan.

305
00:16:39,650 --> 00:16:41,620
I already have a solid foundation.

306
00:16:41,620 --> 00:16:42,180
Great.

307
00:16:44,350 --> 00:16:45,450
Let's go to school then.

308
00:16:46,350 --> 00:16:48,750
Sorry, excuse me.

309
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:58,550
I got up on time but fell asleep between the bedsheets.

310
00:16:58,670 --> 00:17:00,930
We'll discuss everything later, I'm just going to the storage room.

311
00:17:01,090 --> 00:17:02,130
But Ozzak's already sleeping there.

312
00:17:02,510 --> 00:17:03,030
How come?

313
00:17:03,650 --> 00:17:06,950
I tried to wake him but he said it's all Simona's fault.

314
00:17:07,950 --> 00:17:10,690
We had quite a wild night.

315
00:17:10,950 --> 00:17:12,750
Well, not that kind of wild, as you might think.

316
00:17:15,850 --> 00:17:18,620
I left a bit of a mess in the bathroom, but Sasa will clean it up.

317
00:17:18,620 --> 00:17:20,380
Well, the first time didn't go so smoothly.

318
00:17:20,620 --> 00:17:22,360
Look, next time we need to communicate better.

319
00:17:22,420 --> 00:17:24,020
I'm too old for these nighttime escapades.

320
00:17:24,080 --> 00:17:25,580
And I'm old school at that.

321
00:17:25,740 --> 00:17:27,360
But we can't do this all night.

322
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:27,780
What about the kids?

323
00:17:28,080 --> 00:17:28,660
What about them?

324
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:30,620
They fell asleep on the landing on the way to school.

325
00:17:30,780 --> 00:17:33,020
They'll get used to the chaos and so will you, you'll see.

326
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:33,780
Bye then.

327
00:17:38,950 --> 00:17:41,630
Do you have sleeping pills, Marcelka?

328
00:17:44,450 --> 00:17:52,350
Hail, master and lord, accept this kiss from me.

329
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:55,860
Begone, you cruel betrayer!

330
00:17:58,820 --> 00:17:59,440
What?

331
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:02,350
She's been saying for three days it can be changed to a kiss on the mouth.

332
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,720
I am Jesus, does anyone have a problem with that?

333
00:18:07,980 --> 00:18:08,420
No.

334
00:18:10,150 --> 00:18:11,650
Lexa, you've lost it.

335
00:18:14,550 --> 00:18:16,050
I'm done with this!

336
00:18:16,150 --> 00:18:19,750
The only one who kisses me is my sister, and when I finally got clean socks, she washes my feet.

337
00:18:20,950 --> 00:18:22,390
I'm done with this too!

338
00:18:22,850 --> 00:18:27,090
I just walked down the street in costume and some nun spat in front of me.

339
00:18:27,090 --> 00:18:29,290
Why can't I play someone people actually like?

340
00:18:29,590 --> 00:18:33,330
Jesus, I'm also not thrilled about playing a prostitute who washes men's feet.

341
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:34,960
But the dress rehearsal is tomorrow.

342
00:18:35,220 --> 00:18:36,180
I'm going to bed.

343
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:39,550
And what about your plan for a peaceful night?

344
00:18:39,950 --> 00:18:44,750
I'll take this, lock myself in the bedroom, and you do whatever you want.

345
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:46,150
That's exactly what mom would say.

346
00:18:46,150 --> 00:18:49,990
It's some Croatian medication and supposedly works very fast.

347
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:51,990
So if you need anything...

348
00:18:52,150 --> 00:18:54,050
I need this to be over.

349
00:18:56,190 --> 00:18:56,710
Dad?

350
00:18:58,550 --> 00:19:02,250
I think it's already working.

351
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:40,350
Right, I'm taking the room.

352
00:20:14,850 --> 00:20:16,550
Good morning, Krakorova, social services.

353
00:20:24,450 --> 00:20:25,150
You must be Igor.

354
00:20:38,850 --> 00:20:43,750
Do you have any supervision here?

355
00:20:52,850 --> 00:20:54,050
You slept here?

356
00:20:55,460 --> 00:20:56,020
Good God.

357
00:21:07,650 --> 00:21:09,800
Good morning, Krakorova, social services.

358
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:11,260
I'm looking for Simona Buckova.

359
00:21:11,860 --> 00:21:12,980
Simona is still at the pub.

360
00:21:15,450 --> 00:21:16,350
Are you her partner?

361
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:21,400
Boy, you're really out of it today.

362
00:21:22,520 --> 00:21:24,720
May I ask where you're coming from?

363
00:21:25,850 --> 00:21:28,450
Jesus, from the pub, what kind of questions are these.

364
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:31,240
Good morning.

365
00:21:38,050 --> 00:21:39,170
Mrs. Buckova.

366
00:21:39,170 --> 00:21:39,990
Good morning.

367
00:21:41,050 --> 00:21:42,630
Krakorova, social services.

368
00:21:43,250 --> 00:21:45,350
It's even worse than I expected.

369
00:21:45,770 --> 00:21:49,930
Your children are so deprived of a male role model that they're gluing on beards.

370
00:21:49,930 --> 00:21:59,750
And secondly, you come home from the pub in the morning, your partner with you, and you lock your mentally handicapped relative in a closet unsupervised.

371
00:22:01,550 --> 00:22:02,750
You were in the closet?

372
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:03,680
Not yet.

373
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:06,160
So who is your partner then?

374
00:22:06,220 --> 00:22:08,160
This man or this poor fellow?

375
00:22:12,750 --> 00:22:18,350
Mrs. Krakorova, I work as a barmaid in a very dangerous establishment.

376
00:22:18,850 --> 00:22:26,750
And my partner, out of concern for my health and safety, spends my work hours there with me.

377
00:22:27,450 --> 00:22:28,250
You know, darling?

378
00:22:28,250 --> 00:22:32,100
And Igor here sleeps in the closet only when he wants to.

379
00:22:32,450 --> 00:22:34,250
You like the closet, don't you, Igor?

380
00:22:40,950 --> 00:22:43,280
I can, I can.

381
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:46,620
And the children, I just sent them to perform some religious play.

382
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:49,580
Kids, perform a little bit for us.

383
00:22:50,450 --> 00:22:58,450
Oh, dear mother, be not afraid.

384
00:22:58,650 --> 00:23:00,920
Your dear son bears the cross himself.

385
00:23:01,150 --> 00:23:03,250
Before him and behind him walk the executioners.

386
00:23:04,150 --> 00:23:06,150
You can't keep him safe.

387
00:23:06,850 --> 00:23:10,610
You should have written on that questionnaire straight away that you're practicing Christians.

388
00:23:10,610 --> 00:23:12,850
That would have put things in a different light.

389
00:23:13,030 --> 00:23:13,810
We're Hussites.

390
00:23:14,790 --> 00:23:17,750
Well then, let's go sign the paperwork right away.

391
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:19,150
I won't keep you.

392
00:23:19,230 --> 00:23:21,110
The play is sure to be wonderful.

393
00:23:21,410 --> 00:23:23,530
Well yeah, except he doesn't know a single line.

394
00:23:23,790 --> 00:23:24,530
I know one.

395
00:23:24,730 --> 00:23:25,470
Yeah? Which one?

396
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:29,800
Father, father, why hast thou forsaken me?

397
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:33,280
Don't worry, children's opinions don't matter to us.

398
00:23:39,250 --> 00:23:42,450
That was lucky that Krakorova has a soft spot for Jesus.

399
00:23:43,150 --> 00:23:44,550
It doesn't matter anymore anyway.

400
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:48,080
So Libor didn't give up?

401
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:49,260
Oh he did, he gave up.

402
00:23:49,850 --> 00:23:52,450
When he found out how much a kid costs per year, he got a sheep instead.

403
00:23:52,450 --> 00:23:53,580
Baa.

404
00:23:58,750 --> 00:23:59,550
Just in case.

405
00:24:03,130 --> 00:24:04,170
Zoran's pills!

406
00:24:04,650 --> 00:24:05,590
Are you alright?

407
00:24:05,850 --> 00:24:06,450
Yeah.

408
00:24:06,710 --> 00:24:09,750
Now I am, but does Zoran take these often?

409
00:24:10,090 --> 00:24:14,310
They say, since he completed that anger management therapy, at most once or twice a day.

410
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:16,240
What?

411
00:24:17,250 --> 00:24:19,290
Aren't you ever afraid of him?

412
00:24:19,410 --> 00:24:22,330
At most once or twice a day.

413
00:24:24,050 --> 00:24:24,610
Right.

414
00:24:30,850 --> 00:24:34,750
Hail, master and lord, accept this kiss from me.

415
00:24:40,450 --> 00:24:42,550
You have betrayed me with a kiss.

416
00:24:46,950 --> 00:24:48,750
We shall never abandon Jesus!

417
00:24:48,750 --> 00:24:49,390
Love wins!

418
00:24:54,750 --> 00:24:55,950
Marry me!
